item.title: Help with server (no newbs)
item.dc:creator: @frugoo_scape frugoo scape
item.description:
@frugoo_scape wrote:

Frugoo Scape tells you:
You need to check your settings on your computer or your router. If you are behind a router, you will have to configure it. Enabling a port will allow the router to send the port to a specific computer. Also, if you don’t have a router and are having this problem you many want to check your firewall settings. Window’s Firewall has its own little app that blocks ports and you will have to unblock them. If you need detailed help you can post it on my forums. I will be willing to give a better response there. The link is in my sig.

Choose a password

Tell your friends to join that network on hamachi (They must have it to)
Then the IP at the top of hamachi is the IP they will log into your server with

item.title: Help with server (no newbs)
item.dc:creator: @Hell_Hound_0516 Hell Hound 0516
item.description:
@Hell_Hound_0516 wrote:

Make sure they have joined your hamachi network, and make sure they also have the correct port to log in.
And make sure they have the correct IP.
What i mean by a port is on moparisthebest.com
go to file, add port, tell them to add the correct port

To find the correct port open up your Server.java and search for 43594 as a port or 5555 as a port.
if you find one of the 2, then that one is your port. Good Luck
